There is currently protest action in the Germiston area, near the Goodhope informal settlement on Lower Boksburg and Knights roads, Germiston City News reports.
The residents from the Goodhope informal settlement have once again taken to the streets in a service delivery protest.
READ MORE:Â Fighting taxi owners to resume talks in Ekurhuleni
Lower Boksburg Road and Knights Road are closed to traffic as a result of the protest.
Motorists are advised to avoid the area.
The EMPD and SAPS are on scene.
